      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Panorama photograph of a neoclassical building. Some people in urban clothes are in the streets. Title in Bulgarian and French.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The building of Bulgaria's National Theatre, designed by Viennese theatre architects Hermann Helmer and Ferdinand Fellner, was finished in 1906 and opened on 3 January 1907. The building was extensively damaged by a fire in 1923 during an anniversary celebration, but was reconstructed in 1929 by German architect Martin Dülfer. Recto in the lower left corner: "Neubert" - probably the publisher. In the lower right corner: stamp with the name of the photographer.</ab>
